*8th Australasian Society for Cognitive Science Conference -- ASCS 2007

**Second Call for Papers*

9-12 July 2007
University of Adelaide, Australia

 
Offers of papers and posters can be made by *submitting an abstract 
*using our on-line submission system 
<http://ascs.conference-services.net/authorlogin.asp?conferenceID=983&language=en-uk>. 
The final deadline for submission is *1st June 2007*. Please do not 
submit full papers - acceptance of your paper or poster will be based on 
your abstract. If you are offering a paper, please indicate whether you 
prefer your session to be /short /(20 min + 5 min Q&A) or /long /(40 min 
+ 10 min Q&A). See the conference website 
<http://www.arts.adelaide.edu.au/humanities/ascs2007/> for further details.

*Confirmed Speakers

*
*Professor Jeff Elman*
Department of Cognitive Science
University of California, San Diego 	*Professor Kim Sterelny*
Philosophy Program, Research School of Social Sciences
The Australian National University
*Professor Jeffry B. Stock*
Department of Molecular Biology
Princeton University 	*Associate Professor John Sutton*
Department of Philosophy
Macquarie University

*
**Symposia**
*

   1. *Computation and the Mind.*/ //Convener/: Elizabeth Schier,
      Philosophy, University of Adelaide.
   2. *Individual and Group Cognition. */Convenor/: Associate Professor
      Amanda Barnier, MACCS, Macquarie University.
   3. *Toward a Cognitive Biology. */Convener/: Dr Pamela Lyon,
      Philosophy, University of Adelaide. /Participants:/ Fred Keijzer,
      University of Groningen; Ulrike Mathesius, Australian National
      University; Pamela Lyon, University of Adelaide;Jon Opie,
      University of Adelaide.
   4. *Author Meets Critics:*/ /Michael Devitt's "Ignorance of Language"
      (OUP, 2006). Please contact Jon Opie
      <mailto:cogsci01@adelaide.edu.au> if you would like to participate.

*Conference Theme*

The theme of the meeting is *Reconsidering the Foundations of the 
Cognitive Sciences.* We aim to consider such questions as:

    * *What is Cognition? *Which thermodynamic, functional, or adaptive
      criteria distinguish cognitive systems from other physical
      systems? Is cognition a computational or a biological phenomenon,
      or both? What is required for cognitive agency?
    * *What is Representation? *Is representation a capacity of all
      biological systems, or only of organisms with a nervous system?
      How is cognitive representation related to the representing
      systems used in human communication and problem solving?
    * *What is Computation? *Is computation a general feature of
      physical systems, including non-living ones? Is rules and symbols
      (digital) style computation necessary for cognition? What forms of
      computation are realized in neural/biological systems?
    * *What is Language?* Are all cognitive systems sign users? Is
      language the foundation for thought? To what extent is linguistic
      meaning shaped by human sensory and motor capacities? Should
      linguistics concern itself with the physical mechanisms of
      language use?
    * *What is Reasoning? *What styles of representation and computation
      are implicated in reasoning? Are Bayesian models adequate to the
      features of natural reason? How do affective, perceptual, and
      motor processes, and mind-world interactions bear on human reasoning?
    * *What is Consciousness?* What is the function of consciousness? Is
      all conscious experience representational? What is the
      relationship between conscious and unconscious processes in the brain?

*Website*

    http://www.arts.adelaide.edu.au/humanities/ascs2007/

